Uses of Interface
com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.interfaces.Logging

  • Packages that use Logging 
    Package Description
    com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.interfaces
    This package contains some interfaces, that are unique to NetCom2, but not to any sub-package So, for example, some of those interface define a bridge between 2 decoupled parts, some expanded interface of the function package, such as TriConsumer or TriPredicate, which all may be used freely outside of NetCom2.
    com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.logging
    This package contains the NetCom2 logging API, which is used in all other modules within NetCom2.
    com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.interfaces
    This package contains interfaces, that are relevant for both the server and the client package.
    com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.shared  
    com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.shared.clients
    This is the core package for Communication.

      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  CallerReflectionLogging
      This logging implementation uses reflection to determine the caller of any method.
      class  DebugLogging
      This implementation of Logging ignores the trace method
      class  DisabledLogging
      This Logging implementation ignores all calls and logs nothing.
      class  ErrorLogging
      This Logging implementation ignores all calls up to error()
      class  InfoLogging
      This Logging implementation ignores all calls up to info
      class  NetComLogging
      This class is the central entry point for the NetCom2Logging api.
      class  SystemDefaultStyleLogging
      This Class defines how NetCom2 logging looks.
      class  TraceLogging
      This is an instance of Logging, that logs every step.
      class  WarnLogging
      This logging implementation ignores all calls up to warn

      Methods in com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.interfaces that return Logging 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static Logging Logging.callerTrace()
      Creates a logging-level of trace, but analyses the Stacktrace to find the caller of that method.
      static Logging Logging.debug()
      Creates the debug logging-level (does not log trace calls).
      static Logging Logging.disabled()
      Creates a logging-level, that does not log anything
      static Logging Logging.error()
      Creates the debug logging-level (does not log trace, debug, info and warn calls).
      static Logging Logging.getDefault()
      Creates the default logging-level.
      static Logging Logging.info()
      Creates the info logging-level (does not log trace and debug calls).
      static Logging Logging.trace()
      Creates the trace logging-level (logs everything).
      static Logging Logging.unified()
      Creates logging instance, that updates with the NetComLogging.setLogging(Logging) instance
      static Logging Logging.warn()
      Creates the debug logging-level (does not log trace, debug and info calls).
